Sighting Update:

\n\n

\xc2\xb7      \nKey Sightings:

o  \n [2016_WW44\nBKC][BIOS:106_D11][Neon city FPGA]Occasionally cat error and hang at code \'A9\'\nduring warmboot cycling tests 5345509

o      \n[2016_WW43\nBKC][BIOS:105_D11][Neon city FPGA] Cannot enter OS after enable VT-d in BIOS 5345474

 

\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n

\xc2\xb7        Full sighting list can be found in HSD

P&P Update:

Generic Summary:

1. Changed Memory from 32GB 2400MHz to 32GB 2666MHz for Performance test from WW48.

2. Run NLB with Linux kernel 4.7.0, other tests are running with Linux Kernel 3.10.0

3. Runing NLB GBS mode 0 lpbk1 to exercise 2 sockets simultaneously for NLB loading power test.

4. Changed CPU from QLGZ(ES2) to QL66(VIS) for power and performance test from WW47.

5. Target for all test items are not ready, But OSS need target to generate report, so we just use WW43\'s data as target.

6. FPGA power workload: NLB

7. Core performance workloads: Mlc, Linpack, Stream.

WW48:

a) No regression issue found

b) Changed Memory from 32GB 2400MHz to 32GB 2666MHz for memory test.

c) MLC 100 percent rd core2mem BW (GB per sec) score increased around 8.9% due to memory changing to higher frequency one.

d) For HSD[5345552] [2016_WW46 BKC][BIOS 108.D11][P&P][Neon City FPGA] Mlc Local all read memory peak Bandwidth decreased 13.74% (from 182.9 GB/s to 157.6 GB/s )

        -->Verify with B0 VIS QL66 CPU, the regression is 1.72%, cause the change list 435688 has much impact on B0 ES2 QLGZ CPU only, so downgrade this HSD to medium. and wait for H0 CPU to verify.
